header.gameNote: GREAT ALASKA SHOOTOUT AT ANCHORAGE AK

article.headline: Air Force 62, Butler 61
article.story:
ANCHORAGE, Alaska (AP) -- Pamela Findlay scored the go-ahead
basket with 5.4 seconds left and Air Force defeated Butler 62-61
Wednesday for third place in the Carrs/Safeway Great Alaska
Shootout.

The Falcons (2-2) overcame the late-game heroics of Butler
freshman Susan Lester, who scored her team's final 11 points and
gave the Bulldogs (1-3) their only lead of the game, 61-60, with
17.8 seconds remaining.

A day after losing to Division II Alaska-Anchorage and shooting
just 32 percent, Air Force pulled away early and built a 19-point
lead, 30-11, on a basket by Jacki Novak with 6:14 remaining in the
first half.

The Falcons dominated inside, getting repeated second scoring
chances and finished with 21 offensive rebounds.

Butler chipped away at the lead and closed the half on an 11-3
run, capped by a free throw and basket by Mel Thornton and a
3-pointer by Lester to trail 33-27.

A pair of drives by Ellen Hamilton helped Butler close to 55-50
with 5:08 remaining.

Lester then scored on a reverse layup, a 3-pointer, a putback
and a layup before point guard Jackie Closser drove the lane and
fed her for another layup with 17.8 seconds left to give the
Bulldogs their only lead, 61-60.

Air Force moved the ball the length of the court and Findlay
scored on a scoop shot from the baseline.

Butler had one last chance but Closser's runner rolled out at
the buzzer.

The Falcons out-rebounded Butler 51-27 but the Bulldogs blocked
11 shots, including four by Cassie Freeman.

Dawn Higginbotham came off the bench to lead Air Force with 13
points. Findlay and Novak had 11. Findlay added 12 rebounds and
Alecia Steele had 10.

Lester finished with 16 points. Closser had 13 and Hamilton had
11.
